- Add polygon drawing function poly() with variadic template parameters

26.1.3 - 2026-04-22
- Add common color macros (BMP_BLACK, BMP_WHITE, BMP_RED, etc.)

26.1.2 - 2026-04-20
- Now you can give the function a class "Point"

26.1.1 - 2026-04-20
- Now when you init a BMP, it will be white, not black

26.1.0 - 2026-04-19
- Initial official release (version 26.1.0)
- Implement core framebuffer management with dynamic memory allocation
- Add putPixel function for basic pixel rendering (with boundary checking)
- Integrate Bresenham line algorithm for line drawing
- Add rect function for hollow rectangle rendering
- Implement midpoint circle algorithm for circ function (hollow circle)
- Add saveBMP function to export 24-bit RGB BMP image files
- Encapsulate all functions under BMPDraw namespace for namespace isolation
- Add complete header guard (BMPDRAW_H) to prevent multiple inclusions
- Implement Color struct for RGB color management
- Add clear function to initialize framebuffer with specified color